<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:abv="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Abaev Dictionary: entry <hi rendition="#rend_italic">æmbyjyn</hi></title></titleStmt><xi:include href="../pubstmt.xml" parse="xml"/><sourceDesc><bibl xml:lang="ru"><author>Абаев, Василий Иванович</author>.
                                <title>Историко-этимологический словарь осетинского языка</title>.
                            Т. <biblScope unit="volume">I</biblScope>. A–Kʼ.
                                <pubPlace>М.–Л.</pubPlace>: <publisher>Наука</publisher>,
                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_æmbyjyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>æmbyjyn</orth><form type="participle"><orth>æmbyd</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æmbujun</orth><form type="participle"><orth>æmbud</orth></form></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>гнить</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>rot</q></abv:tr></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>særd dyn mа ʽmbyjænt, zymæg dyn ma sælænt</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пусть у тебя летом не гниют, зимой не замерзают</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>let you not rot in the summer, not freeze in the winter</q></abv:tr><bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">из посвящения покойнику</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">from dedication to a dead person</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>c’yfy wærmy dæ bambyjyn kodton</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>я сгноила тебя в грязной яме</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>I rotted you in a dirty pit</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 40</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*ham-pu-</w></mentioned>, сращение преверба <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/> (← %iham-%i) с корнем %iрū-%i ‘гнить’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>anbūsīdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>pūsīdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>hambūsītan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-pamir" extralang="srh"><lang/> <w>pay-: pūd-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-pamir" extralang="sgh"><lang/> <w>piy-: pud-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/> <w>pū-</w> <gloss><q>гнить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><w>pūduk</w> <gloss><q>гнилой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/> <w>рīо</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>pītk</w> <gloss><q>гнилой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/> <w>pĭw-: pəd-</w> <gloss><q>гнить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>pū-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>puyeiti</w> <gloss><q>гниет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>a-puyant</w> <gloss><q>не гниющий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>рū-</w> <gloss><q>гниет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>puti</w> <gloss><q>гнить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>πύω</w> <gloss><q>вызываю нагноение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>πύθω</w> <gloss><q>гною</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>pus</w> <gloss><q>гной</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>puteo</w> <gloss><q>гнию</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>putidus</w> <gloss><q>гнилой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/> <w>fūls</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>faul</w> <gloss><q>гнилой</q></gloss></mentioned>. Предшествие %im%i предотвратило обычный для осетинского переход %ip%i → %if%i, но повлекло озвончение %ip%i → %ib%i. Старым каузативом от %iæmbujun%i является %iæmbawun%i q. v. Сюда же <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fawyn"/> ‘хулить’. Ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyd"/> | %ifyd%i ‘дурной’ считаем лексикализованным старым причастием %ipūta-%i ‘гнилой’. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æmbyd"/> ‘гнилой’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>II 85</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>65</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*ham-pu-</w></mentioned>, fusion of the preverb <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/> (← %iham-%i) with the root %iрū-%i ‘rot’. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>anbūsīdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>pūsīdan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>hambūsītan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-pamir" extralang="srh"><lang/> <w>pay-: pūd-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-pamir" extralang="sgh"><lang/> <w>piy-: pud-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/> <w>pū-</w> <gloss><q>rot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><w>pūduk</w> <gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/> <w>рīо</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/> <w>pītk</w> <gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/> <w>pĭw-: pəd-</w> <gloss><q>rot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>pū-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>puyeiti</w> <gloss><q>it rots</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>a-puyant</w> <gloss><q>not rotting</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>рū-</w> <gloss><q>it rots</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>puti</w> <gloss><q>rot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>πύω</w> <gloss><q>I cause suppuration</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>πύθω</w> <gloss><q>I rot (smth.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>pus</w> <gloss><q>pus</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>puteo</w> <gloss><q>I rot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>putidus</w> <gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/> <w>fūls</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>faul</w> <gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>. Precedence of %im%i prevented usual Ossetic alterntation %ip%i → %if%i, but it caused vocalisation %ip%i → %ib%i. An old causative to %iæmbujun%i is %iæmbawun%i q. v. Here too is <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fawyn"/> ‘blaspheme’. We consider the Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyd"/> | %ifyd%i ‘evil’ to be an old lexalized participle %ipūta-%i ‘rotten’. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æmbyd"/> ‘rotten’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>II 85</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>65</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>